        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Hypo- and hypermelanotic cutaneous macules-retarded growth-intellectual disability syndrome is a rare genetic pigmentation anomaly of the skin disorder characterized by congenital hypomelanotic and hypermelanotic cutaneous macules associated with in some patients retarded growth and intellectual disability. There have been no further descriptions in the literature since 1978."
        },
